We use a stroboscopic representation of motion to draw the dynamics of the relevant atoms involved in the various processes: the atoms and the bonds are coloured in red at the beginning of the process and, passing by the green, become blue at the end. The barrier associated with each stage is also reported in Fig. 4. Panels a, b, d, e, and e–g show the migration of A+ and X- for the MAPbI3, MAPbBr3 and FAPbBr3 system, respectively. Panels c, f represent the reorganization stage of the process in which MAI-PbI2 and MA-PbBr2 transform into MAPI3 and MAPBr3, respectively.

